  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through several key strategies:\n\n1. Detection Methods\n- Financial transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n- Advanced data analytics and tracking technologies\n\n2. Legal Frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance requirements\n- Bank Secrecy Act provisions\n- International standards like FATF recommendations\n\n3. Investigation Techniques\n- Forensic accounting\n- Digital forensics\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Undercover operations\n- Collaboration between different investigative agencies\n\n4. Prosecution Approaches\n- Seizure of illegal assets\n- Criminal charges\n- Financial penalties\n- International extradition agreements\n\n5. Technological Tools\n- Blockchain analysis\n- Machine learning detection algorithms\n- Cross-border financial tracking systems\n\nThese approaches aim to systematically identify, investigate, and prosecute complex money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
